Why do you need it to be of type `GenericWebApplicationContext`?  
I think you can probably work with any ApplicationContext type.

Usually you would use an init method (in addition to your setter method):

    @PostConstruct
    public void init(){
        AutowireCapableBeanFactory bf = this.applicationContext
            .getAutowireCapableBeanFactory();
        // wire stuff here
    }

And you would wire beans by using either 

[`AutowireCapableBeanFactory.autowire(Class, int mode, boolean dependencyInject)`][1]

or

[`AutowireCapableBeanFactory.initializeBean(Object existingbean, String beanName)`][2]


  [1]:http://static.springsource.org/spring/docs/3.0.x/javadoc-api/org/springframework/beans/factory/config/AutowireCapableBeanFactory.html#autowire%28java.lang.Class%2C%20int%2C%20boolean%29%20
  [2]: http://static.springsource.org/spring/docs/3.0.x/javadoc-api/org/springframework/beans/factory/config/AutowireCapableBeanFactory.html#initializeBean%28java.lang.Object%2C%20java.lang.String%29

